South African artist Esther Mahlangu. AFP/Gulshan Khan JOHANNESBURG - A R50,000 reward has been issued for credible information that could lead to an arrest and conviction in connection with the house robbery of renowned artist Ester Mahlangu The national icon was robbed and assaulted in her home in Weldervrede near Siyabuswa on 19 March. The artist was robbed of her personal firearm and an undisclosed amount of money. Police have urged anyone with information regarding the robbery to come forward.